column4: JOB TITLE: Junior Investment Data Analyst Location: St. Louis, Missouri COMPANY: ACR Alpine Capital Research, LLC is a $4.5B+ AUM fundamental value manager serving financial intermediaries and institutions with concentrated equity, credit, and multi-strategy vehicles. ACR is headquartered in St.Louis, Missouri. For additional information, please visit www.acr-invest.com. RESPONSIBILITIES: The candidate will be responsible for supporting the investment team in the acquisition and maintenance of company, industry, economic, portfolio, and performance data. Relocation to St. Louis and 50-hour work week required. Investment Team Support:  QUALIFICATIONS: The successful candidate will be a very well read, highly curious, independent thinking, rational, and self-starting investment professional. COMPENSATION: Competitive compensation commensurate with qualifications and performance. Job Type: Full-time Benefits: Schedule: COVID-19 considerations:All in office employees must be fully vaccinated. Work Location: One location Maintain portfolio and financial reports, and economic databank/chartbook created from multiple sources. Support the production of investment presentations, quarterly letters, and other firm collateral. Support the research, composition, and underlying data-acquisition needs for white papers. Manage and coordinate data collection from disparate sources including CapIQ, Bloomberg, Factset, FRED, industry publications, and portfolio/accounting software. Lead quality control efforts and validation of data accuracy. Apply intellectual curiosity to identify and flag the reasonableness of data outliers. Help develop and produce new and incremental reports and dashboards for use by the investment team. Gather and synthesize difficult-to-find data on industries, companies, and markets. Assist with maintenance of financial models and company research on an ad hoc basis. Acquire competency in the firm’s investment principles and process. Demonstrate desire to learn new financial skills and software tools as needed in an unstructured environment. Highest level of integrity and ethical standards. Strong working knowledge of business, finance, accounting, and economics. Interest in big data and knowledge of R, Python (SciPy, NumPy), APIs, or other programming abilities a plus. A passion for value investing and desire to read key value investment books. Excellent analytical and critical thinking skills. Very detail oriented. Expertise in Microsoft Excel desired. Minimum bachelor’s degree or equivalent. Open to recent graduates as well as those with industry experience. Preferred backgrounds include finance, accounting, economics, statistics, or data science. Desire to pursue CFA or other investment/data designation a plus. 401(k) 401(k) matching Dental insurance Employee assistance program Flexible spending account Health insurance Life insurance Paid time off Parental leave Referral program Vision insurance Monday to Friday

The California Public Employees’ Retirement System (CalPERS) is the nation’s largest public pension fund, providing retirement and health benefits to public employees, retirees, and their families. Headquartered in downtown Sacramento, we are a destination employer with an international reputation for leadership and innovation. At CalPERS, we’re committed to people – the people we serve, our team members, and the larger community around us. CalPERS is situated near the Napa Valley, San Francisco, Lake Tahoe, and other desirable destinations, and we offer competitive benefit packages, compensation, and opportunities for advancement. Our Human Resources Division is currently seeking a Research Data Analyst I/II with a working title of Workforce Data Analyst to support CalPERS with HR data gathering, analysis, and enterprise-wide workforce planning support and services. The Workforce Data Analyst is part of a team of technical professionals within the WDA team. This team is highly visible and frequently partners with senior and executive level leaders to provide enterprise-wide support for CalPERS Workforce Planning, HR data analysis, and oversight of all HR technology projects and systems. The ideal candidate will have a strong mix of experience and well-developed skills in written and oral communication, best practice research, complex Excel formulas, performing quantitative and qualitative data-driven research and statistical analysis, and problem solving. Primary responsibilities will include planning, organizing, and conducting studies in a variety of areas which affect HR programs or system development. This position requires an enthusiastic, forward-thinking analyst with a strong eye for detail. The incumbent is responsible for producing data reports for senior leaders, the preparation and delivery of presentations, and the development of multimedia marketing materials. The Workforce Data Analyst is also responsible for developing innovative strategies and tactics in support of WDA and CalPERS’ strategic objectives, business plan initiatives, and the CalPERS Workforce Plan. Job Type: Full-time Pay: $3,800.00 - $7,079.00 per month Benefits: Schedule: Work Location: One location 401(k) Dental insurance Flexible schedule Health insurance Paid time off Parental leave Professional development assistance Retirement plan Vision insurance 8 hour shift

Who we are: At PayPal (NASDAQ: PYPL), we believe that every person has the right to participate fully in the global economy. Our mission is to democratize financial services to ensure that everyone, regardless of background or economic standing, has access to affordable, convenient, and secure products and services to take control of their financial lives. We’re a purpose-driven company, and our beliefs are the foundation of how we conduct business every day. We’re guided by our core values of Inclusion, Innovation, Collaboration, and Wellness. Collectively, these values inspire us to work together as One Team with our customers at the center of everything we do, and to take care of ourselves, each other, and the communities in which we live and work. We challenge the status quo, ask questions, and find solutions. Join us as we enable the hopes, dreams, and ambitions of millions of people around the world. Join us as we enable the hopes, dreams, and ambitions of millions of people around the world Job Description:  • Create consumer risk policies, strategies and experience to support PayPal growth while ensuring alignment with financial and reputational risk appetite. • Proactively identifies, investigates, and resolves most issues and problems that may impact all components of work.  • Conduct on-going strategy performance analytics and communicate strategy design and result to senior management • Work with product managers and engineering team in deploying risk decisioning strategies, designing new product capabilities, enhancing systems • Trouble-shooting any data, system and flow challenge while maintaining flawless strategy execution  For more than 20 years, PayPal has remained at the forefront of the digital payment revolution. By leveraging technology to make financial services and commerce more convenient, affordable, and secure, our open digital payments platform gives PayPal’s 400 million active account holders the confidence to connect and transact in new and powerful ways. Through a combination of technological innovation and strategic partnerships, PayPal creates better ways to manage and move money, and offers choice and flexibility when sending payments, paying, or getting paid. Available in more than 200 markets around the world, the PayPal platform, including Braintree, Venmo and Xoom, enables consumers and merchants to receive money in more than 100 currencies, withdraw funds in 56 currencies and hold balances in their PayPal accounts in 25 currencies. PayPal provides equal employment opportunity (EEO) to all persons regardless of age, color, national origin, citizenship status, physical or mental disability, race, religion, creed, gender, sex, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, genetic information, marital status, status with regard to public assistance, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local law. In addition, PayPal will provide reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities. Focuses significantly on providing the appropriate framing of business problems, making critical design decisions, defining project plans and work breakdowns, setting timelines and quality metrics for the project, and coordinating activities of cross-functional teams to deliver effective solutions.  Apply statistical techniques and strategy solutions to predict and manage consumer risk associated with PayPal products and accounts For each decisioning strategy project, design its best structure and select the most appropriate techniques which may include a combination of several techniques  Master degree or above in Engineering, Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Finance or related fields.  Strong logical thinking capability. Understanding of various analytical and modeling methods is a strong plus.  Strong software programming skills and familiar with at least one programming language. Do you love digging into data to draw conclusions? Do your friends tell you your love of spreadsheets is a little excessive? Does working for a Digital Marketing agency with huge growth opportunities sound cool? We're looking for YOU! City Ranked is looking for an analytical mind who loves identifying trends in data, tracking performance, is a whiz with data visualization. We'd love to find someone well-versed in the SEO landscape, but this could also be a great opportunity for a driven individual who has always wanted to explore Digital Marketing to enter the field. What's the job entail? Requirements for the position? Who is City Ranked, anyway? We're a local Digital Marketing company, here in Vancouver WA; and when we say local, we mean it - we pride ourselves on doing everything in-house. Our team of 25 marketing experts bring knowledge from various fields to the table, including design and development, paid search, search engine optimization, programming, content writing, marketing analytics, and relationship management. Everyone here takes their work seriously without taking themselves too seriously; it's a fun team. We prioritize ongoing education, research, and testing, and measure our success solely by the growth of our clients' businesses. In the past three years, we've been ranked in the Top 50 nationwide in our industry - in 2021 we're #6 in the nation for Enterprise Search. Our employees are the most important part of our business, and we constantly work to cultivate an atmosphere of learning, teamwork, and personal/professional growth. We offer great benefits (medical, dental, vision, 401k), a flexible work schedule, on-the-job personal training hours, regular team-building events, and a company gym membership! ﻿If you like analyzing raw data sets, measuring results, and drawing conclusions -- we want you to join our team! Research shows that women and underrepresented groups only apply to jobs only if they think they meet 100% of the qualifications on a job description. IMO is committed to considering all candidates even if you don’t think you meet 100% of the qualifications listed. We look forward to receiving your application! Work that is meaningful. A job that has impact. Colleagues that inspire. That’s what you’ll find at Intelligent Medical Objects (IMO), a growing health IT company creating clinical terminology and insights solutions that are used by more than 500,000 US physicians and 4,500 US hospitals to power better patient care and support meaningful analytics. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis of database and scripting discrepancies within IMO's terminology database. The data analyst provides analysis, research, and resolution to quality issues in regard to IMO database, scripting of queries, as well has implementation and development of processes for IMO’s content infrastructure. This can include coordinating content development with IMO terminology release cycles. The Data Analyst also supports the design, development, maintenance, documentation and testing of scripting for IMO terminology infrastructure. This isn't your everyday analyst - IMO's 'data' is our terminology - and the work of the Data Analyst here at IMO has a huge impact on our our clients interact with our products. Ensuring the quality of the database and process infrastructure is key to the success of the Data Analyst at IMO. Not only will you develop advanced scripting and analytics skills, but you'll come to know a wide array of medical and clinical terminology that will set you apart from your peers in analytics. Responsibilities Requirements #LI-PL1 #LI-Remote At IMO, we celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. IMO is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. Partnering with you to live your best life. At Centra, we want to listen carefully and get to know you well. We want to understand your hopes, goals and dreams. The Company The Maine Cannabis Campus is the first vertically integrated, state and municipality licensed, adult and medical use cannabis company in Maine. Due to our 9 years of experience in the medical cannabis industry we have been able to perfect our cannabis products to a medicinal level. This begins with the highest quality cultivation facilities and flower, allowing us to transfer that consistent quality to our recreational customers. Our passion is about educating and integrating within our communities to diminish the misguided stigma that has been floating around cannabis vs. opioid uses & abuse for much too long. We take great care in making sure our customers only receive the cleanest, most effective products for their individualized needs; along with the peace of mind that their choice was the right one. The positive innovation, opportunity, healing, and community that cannabis brings is undeniable; our intention is to keep it all growing. General summary of role The data analyst role will work directly with the Chief Financial Officer and provide the data compilation and analysis for the company. They will assist in compilation, interpretation, and reporting of key data points throughout all company departments. These departments include cultivation, manufacturing (including processing, packaging, and commercial kitchen operations), retail, and admin/financial. This is a critical role, whose main objective is to offer valuable information to aid in decision making on micro and macro levels company wide. - Extracting, transforming, and storing data from multiple departments for analysis and comparison over time. - Maintaining a level of knowledge on data sets from multiple departments to interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets. - Actively partnering with departments throughout the company to seek out various data points and compile weekly overview reports for executive leadership. - Assisting with various projects laid out by the Chief Financial Officer Job requirements - Bachelor’s degree (Preferably with an accounting, business, computer science or economics focus) - Highly proficient in Excel & QuickBooks - Experience creating data visualizations in excel - Background and understanding of accounting principles is preferred - Exceptional verbal and written communication skills - Strong mathematics skills and attention to detail to aid in compiling and interpreting large and complex data sets Job Type: Full-time Pay: $55,000.00 - $65,000.00 per year Benefits: Physical Setting: Schedule: Ability to commute/relocate: Education: Experience: Work Location: One location Dental insurance Health insurance Paid time off Vision insurance Office 8 hour shift Day shift Fairfield, ME 04937: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required) Bachelor's (Required) SQL: 1 year (Preferred)

column2: Assistant Data Analyst, Rankings and Contests
column4: Engineering News-Record (ENR), the leading source of news and data for a community of over 400,000 construction industry professionals, is looking for an experienced data analyst or data journalist to work with a team of editors to produce top ranking lists and content. Like the Fortune 500 in general business, the ENR regional and national Top Lists are well-known—and essential—to construction professionals. The successful candidate will work to set up surveys to collect data from industry firms in 10 regional sectors, and then disseminate the surveys via marketing outreach, email, phone calls, social media and other means to prospective participants. Next, the staff member will analyze the data and work with ENR editors to produce firm rankings and other content. The second key responsibility will be managing the data underpinnings of ENR’s many competitions and contests using Open Water. Experience should include experience in data analysis and the ability to integrate data with journalism. Experience working on the staff of a newspaper, website, consumer magazine or B2B journal is a plus. Candidates should be comfortable with and have aptitude for working with data and with programs such as Oracle, SQL, Excel, OpenWater, or others. Basic understanding of marketing is helpful. Candidates should demonstrate good news judgment as well as the ability to collaborate efficiently in a team environment under deadline pressure. An understanding of construction, engineering, technology and business is helpful. Job Requirements · Managing the data underpinnings of ENR’s many competitions and contests using OpenWater. Website Other Job Type: Full-time Pay: $55,000.00 - $60,000.00 per year Benefits: Schedule: Experience: Work Location: Remote Familiarity with database programs (MS Access, Oracle or others) and Excel spreadsheets is essential Experience in SQL and writing queries Ability to multitask and manage dozens of lists, rankings and contests throughout the year Work with others members of the surveys and rankings team to integrate regional and national top list databases and allow participants to more easily submit data both regionally and nationally. column3: Government of the District of Columbia
column4: Bring your professional career to Washington, D.C., the most dynamic and diverse city in the country. With its proximity to major museums, world class parks, entertainment, and restaurants, increasing job opportunities and the seat of the federal government, the District of Columbia continues to be ranked in the top 10 of thriving city indicators where you can live, work and play. Contribute to and work for a nationally accredited Health Department. The District of Columbia Department of Health (DC Health) earned national accreditation by the Public Health Accreditation Board (PHAB) and is an early adopter in attaining the designation. Come see where your skills are appreciated and rewarded by applying for the following public health opportunity.  This position is in the Department of Health (DC Health), Community Health Administration (CHA), Health Care Access Bureau (HCAB). CHA promotes healthy behaviors and healthy environments to improve health outcomes and reduce disparities in the leading causes of mortality and morbidity in the District. CHA focuses on population health strategies to prevent and control cancer, chronic disease, and vaccine preventable diseases; promote nutrition and physical fitness; ensure access to quality health care services; and support the health and well-being of families across the lifespan. CHA’s approach targets the behavioral, clinical, and social determinants of health through evidence-based programs, policy, and systems changes.  Major Duties and Responsibilities  The incumbent serves as a data analyst responsible for public-facing COVID-19 dashboards. This position involves accessing, analyzing, and visualizing data related to COVID-19 immunization administration and coverage in the District. The incumbent: keeps abreast of developments in the field of immunizations and vaccine preventable diseases (VPDs); develops internal and external-facing visualizations and reports related to COVID-19 and other immunization status; collaborates with team members to identify and implement innovative analyses or data visualizations to inform program and policy development; as well as to provide actionable information for the general public.  Qualifications and Education  Individuals must possess at least one (1) year of specialized experience must have been equivalent to at least the next lower grade (12) level in the normal line of progression for the occupation in the organization. Specialized experience is defined as experience that is typically in or related to the work of the position to be filled, and has equipped you with the particular knowledge, skills, and abilities to successfully perform the duties of the position, and that is typically in or related to the work of the position to be filled.  Based on the duties and responsibilities of this position, the following are strongly preferred for the incumbent of this position:  A minimum of a master’s in Public Health (MPH), Master of Science in Public Health (MSPH), or equivalent degree and prior work experience in the area of Public Health, specifically related to immunizations administration and coverage visualization. The incumbent must be proficient in utilizing Tableau to develop data dashboards.  Licenses and Certifications  None required.  Working Conditions / Environment  The incumbent must be able to carry out official duties in a variety of settings and conditions. Routine work will occur primarily in an office setting.  Other Significant Facts  Tour of Duty: Monday - Friday 8:15am - 4:45pm  Area of Consideration: Open to the Public  Promotion Potential: No Known Promotion Potential  Pay Plan, Series and Grade: CS-301-13  Collective Bargaining Unit (Union): This position is not covered in a collective bargaining unit.  Position Designation: This position has been designated as Security Sensitive. Pursuant to section 410 of Chapter 4 of the D.C. Personnel Regulations; in addition to the general suitability screening, individuals applying for or occupying security sensitive positions are subject to the following checks and tests:  (a) Criminal background check.  (b) Traffic record check (as applicable).  (c) Consumer credit check (as applicable).  (d) Reasonable suspicion drug and alcohol test; and  (e) Post-accident or incident drug and alcohol test.  Vaccination Requirement: The Government of the District of Columbia values the safety of our employees, our residents, and our visitors. In support of these values, if you are selected for this job you must be fully vaccinated against COVID-19, except when vaccination is not medically advised or violates your sincerely held religious beliefs. If you are invited to join our team, you must submit proof that you are fully vaccinated against COVID-19 to your initial HR representative, or you must request an exemption from your representative. New employees must either provide proof of vaccination or be granted a medical or religious exemption before working with the Government of the District of Columbia.  EEO Statement: The District of Columbia Government is an Equal Opportuning Employer. All qualified candidates will receive consideration without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, sex, age, marital status, personal appearance, sexual orientation, family responsibilities, matriculation, physical handicap, or political affiliation.

The Brain Dynamics Lab (BDL) within the Department of Psychiatry and Behavioral Sciences is seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to manage and analyze large amounts of information, typically technical or scientific in nature, independently with minimal supervision. The candidate will help in the development and maintenance of our toolboxes and processing pipelines. This person will interface with neuroimaging researchers, clinicians, and computational researchers to develop and scale up our current data processing pipelines. The position provides the opportunity for the applicant to participate in state-of-the-art data processing pipeline development within a multi-disciplinary team, whose goal is to develop computational methods for anchoring psychiatric diagnosis into spatiotemporal features of the brain. The BDL is a computational neuropsychiatry lab dedicated to developing computational methods for a better understanding of individual differences in brain functioning in healthy and patient populations. For more information about the lab please visit http://bdl.stanford.edu Duties include: DESIRED QUALIFICATIONS: EDUCATION & EXPERIENCE (REQUIRED): Bachelor's degree or a combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering. KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND ABILITIES (REQUIRED): CERTIFICATIONS & LICENSES: None PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS*: WORKING CONDITIONS: Some work may be performed in a laboratory or field setting. *** As an organization that receives federal funding, Stanford University has a COVID-19 vaccination requirement that will apply to all university employees, including those working remotely in the United States and applicable subcontractors. To learn more about COVID policies and guidelines for Stanford University Staff, please visit https://cardinalatwork.stanford.edu/working-stanford/covid-19/interim-policies/covid-19-surveillance-testing-policy Collect, manage and clean neuroimaging datasets. Employ new and existing neuroimaging data analysis tools (e.g., fMRIprep and XCPengine) to interpret, analyze, and visualize multivariate relationships in data. Create databases and reports, develop algorithms and statistical models, and perform statistical analyses appropriate to data and reporting requirements. Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and determine root cause for data problems from input errors or inadequate field edits, and suggest possible solutions. Develop reports, charts, graphs and tables for use by investigators and for publication and presentation. Analyze data processes in documentation. Collaborate with faculty and research staff on data collection and analysis methods. Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff. Communicate with government officials, grant agencies and industry representatives. - Other duties may also be assigned Bachelors/Masters degree in bioinformatics, computer science, or related fields Experience with MRI imaging analysis Experience with ML/DL  Substantial experience with programming languages such as Matlab and python. Understanding of statistical components underlying neuroimaging processing pipelines. Understanding of digital signal processing. Strong writing and analytical skills. Ability to prioritize workload. Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity. Occasionally use a telephone. Rarely writing by hand. - Consistent with its obligations under the law, the University will provide reasonable accommodation to any employee with a disability who requires accommodation to perform the essential functions of his or her job.
